LNS: 200Hz AUHipass filter applied in soundBlade.  Bird giving continuous calls (singing?) from low hedge along road.

The microphone is oriented on a single female bird.  It is perched on a wire approx. 8 ft. from a single male bird.  At approx. :38, the microphone is oriented on the male bird.  At approx. 1:15 it turns its head approx. 45 degrees away from the microphone.  shortly after this, a second male flies and lands approx. 2 ft. from the original male.  The original male flicks its tail several times and moves towards the second male.  The second male flies off.  Shortly after this, at approx. 1:40, the first male flies off leaving the female by itself.

Two individuals are sitting on a rock vocalizing.  They fly off and two more individuals join them in flight.  They continue to vocalize until they are out of visual contact.    LNS: 100Hz AUHipass filter applied in soundBlade.
